Achieving The Right Balance in Conversational AI Panel just kicked off. Q: Will Chatbots and AI kill jobs? A: Jobs always change and evolve. The use cases for AI are far broader than just call center agents. #c3sf2018

Consumers want personalized answers, not lists of articles.” Great demo of MyPetDoc, which merges AI Voice and Human (veternarian) interaction to help pet parents get answers and make better decisions. #c3sf2018"
beauty
hectic!

Closing Thoughts from Continues Authentication Panel: * Adapting the authentication module to the scenario * Privacy must always be front and center * Biometric is not enough anymore * Is that the right person and is that a person? * Safety is not security #c3sf2018
Data, Trust, and Design: Assistants should help you find your keys, but don’t tell it where your diamond rings are located. #c3sf2018

From E-Commerce to Conversational Commerce - Customers don’t impulse buy a $1000 laptop - 2-week cycle with multiple interaction points. - Voice & messaging for groceries? * Delivery: I’ll be home in 3 hours." * Concierge: "Can you recommend a Pinot under $30." #c3sf2018"
VIP Shops case study about Chatbots in China has been fascinating, the pace of growth around chat and voice based products and experiences in China are astounding and inspiring. #c3sf2018

Takeaways from @cpearl42 - Design starts at the beginning - It matters how the question is asked - When appropriate, give a bit more info-but don’t overdue it - Use personal info when you have permission & its appropriate - Remember things http:// Actions.google.com/design #c3sf2018

Hey Google, when does England play today?” Without context, there is no way for a machine to understand this question. Because this was a planned and designed feature, Google can respond accurately. #worldcup Cathy Pearl @cpearl42 - Head of Conversation Design @Google #c3sf2018"
Closing thoughts from A higher calling for conversational commerce" panel "Conversations are beyond customer service. The future of the website will be a conversation." @mjayleibs #c3sf2018"
People are bringing expectations about how they communicate with friends and family, to their conversations with brands." - @chrismessina #c3sf2018"
Engagement innovation is the next level of digital transformation." - Janine Belvini, @esurance #CX #c3sf2018"

Closing thoughts: - Dissenting voice: don’t go slow, go fast but be pragmatic. - Design for a conversation, design from the consumer perspective. - If you move quickly, make it narrow. If you're moving more slowly, you can be broader. - Hire liberal arts majors. #c3sf2018
#3 Nugget from the panel: Good bots are the result of great design, much more than technology. Hire experts in human psychology such as writers and linguists to help design your bot. #c3sf2018
#2 Nugget: #Amazon now integrates a button bot" to predict and prompt customer’s questions and guide them to the right next step. #c3sf2018"
#1 Nugget of from the panel: Using machine learning in longer conversations with more contextual information helps the machine" learn more effectively. #c3sf2018"
